					<description><![CDATA[<p>Raghu Vamsi Aerospace Group Raises Funding For Global Expansion Hyderabad-based Raghu Vamsi Aerospace Group (RVAG) has raised $40 million to expand its aerospace manufacturing operations and strengthen its deep-tech defence</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/raghu-vamsi-aerospace-group-raises-40m-manufacturing-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Raghu Vamsi Aerospace Group Raises $40M To Expand Aerospace Manufacturing</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Raghu Vamsi Aerospace Group Raises Funding For Global Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hyderabad-based Raghu Vamsi Aerospace Group (RVAG) has raised $40 million to expand its aerospace manufacturing operations and strengthen its </span><a href="https://www.undp.org/policy-centre/singapore/deep-tech-and-innovations" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">deep-tech</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> defence business. It was led by Norwest and Skegen Asset Management, with participation from Indus Bridge Ventures, GJNX Ventures and investor Ashish Kacholia.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It will be used to increase manufacturing capacity across the company&#8217;s facilities in India, the United Kingdom and the United States. RVAG also plans to accelerate construction of its integrated manufacturing campus at Hardware Park while investing further in its Mission Systems and Deep-Tech &amp; Autonomous Systems divisions.</span></p>
<h2><b>Manufacturing Footprint Continues To Grow</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">RVAG has become a global aerospace and defence manufacturer within just over twenty years of operations worldwide. The company employs more than 1,200 people across over ten sites in three countries globally. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It manufactures precision aero-engine parts, sub-assemblies, and specialised components for leading aerospace customers worldwide today. Customers include GE Aerospace, Pratt &amp; Whitney, Honeywell, Safran, and Collins Aerospace across multiple global markets. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">RVAG also supplies engineered components to energy companies including Baker Hughes, Halliburton, SLB, and GE worldwide. Its manufacturing expertise includes product design, engineering, CNC machining, composites, sheet metal fabrication, and electronics integration. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also provides testing, assembly, and advanced manufacturing capabilities supporting aerospace, defence, and energy industries. RVAG reported an order backlog exceeding INR 2,500 crore driven by sustained customer demand across industries. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Managing Director Vamsi Vikas said the investment validates the company&#8217;s vertically integrated manufacturing approach and strategy. He added the funding will expand international operations and accelerate advanced technology programmes for future growth.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investment Strengthens Indigenous Defence Technologies<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203643" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203643" class="size-full wp-image-203643" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-depicting-a-sleek-ad_AYL_G2GQWB635lqHE3WhCA_4htzJOQyStel_JddknL03Q.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing advanced defence systems including drones and aerospace components." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203643" class="wp-caption-text">RVAG expands into deep-tech defence innovation with autonomous systems and advanced aerospace technologies. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond contract manufacturing, RVAG has expanded into developing proprietary defence technologies through its Mission Systems and Deep-Tech business units. The company is developing micro turbojet engines, aircraft hydraulic pumps and missile subsystems for defence programmes. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It is also advancing autonomous technologies through its ARROBOT platform, which focuses on jet-powered drones, internal combustion engine drones and unmanned ground vehicles for India&#8217;s armed forces.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer Siva Arvinth said the funding would enable the company to invest further in technology development, workforce expansion and talent development while building on the principles established by founder G. Thrimurthulu.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">RVAG has also established partnerships with leading Indian academic and research institutions, including the IITs, IIITs, ARCI, ADA and DRDO, to support the development of advanced aerospace and defence technologies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/fora-raises-60m-series-d-ai-travel-advisors/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Fora Raises $60M To Expand AI Platform For Travel Advisors</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Long-Term Aerospace Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Norwest Partner Shiv Chaudhary said RVAG has built an integrated manufacturing platform trusted by global aerospace and energy companies through technical expertise and disciplined execution.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Skegen Asset Management also highlighted the company&#8217;s ability to combine advanced manufacturing with mission systems and deep-tech innovation, positioning it as an important player within India&#8217;s expanding aerospace and defence ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As countries continue investing in defence manufacturing capacity and advanced aerospace technologies, RVAG plans to strengthen its international production capabilities while expanding its portfolio of high-value indigenous defence systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/raghu-vamsi-aerospace-group-raises-40m-manufacturing-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Raghu Vamsi Aerospace Group Raises $40M To Expand Aerospace Manufacturing</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
