					<description><![CDATA[<p>Artificial intelligence is beginning to play a bigger role in the commercial space race. Beijing-based aerospace startup LegendSpace raises $29.5 million (200 million yuan) in a massively successful Angel funding</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/legendspace-raises-29-5-million-ai-rocket-engines/" data-wpel-link="internal">LegendSpace Raises $29.5 Million in Angel Round To Develop AI-Driven Rocket Engines</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Artificial intelligence is beginning to play a bigger role in the commercial space race. Beijing-based aerospace startup LegendSpace raises $29.5 million (200 million yuan) in a massively successful Angel funding round. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LegendSpace was founded just six months ago and is already moving fast to disrupt the traditional space industry. They want to completely reinvent how engineers design and build liquid rocket propulsion systems. By using AI and deep learning instead of slow physical testing, LegendSpace aims to make rocket engineering significantly cheaper.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">LegendSpace Secures $29.5M Just Six Months from Launch</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Securing mega-funding quickly is tough for any new business. It is even tougher in the capital-intensive aerospace sector where returns take years. Yet, LegendSpace completed this massive transaction in record time. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A group of heavy-hitting venture capital firms co-led the early-stage round. Top institutional investors included Oasis Capital, Source Code Rhythm, Shanshi Capital, Tsingyuan Ventures, and Fortune Capital. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Additionally, Cygnus Equity stepped in to serve as the exclusive financial advisor for the deal. This strong financial backing shows immense market confidence in the intersection of AI software and space hardware.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cuspai-raises-450-million-series-b-ai-materials-foundry/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>CuspAI Raises $450M To Launch AI Materials Foundry</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Ditching Prototypes for Deep Learning Systems</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Building a traditional rocket engine is a slow, agonizing process. Legacy aerospace manufacturers typically spend years building expensive physical prototypes. They test them, watch them fail, and tweak the designs over multiple painful iterations. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This happens because liquid-propellant engines operate under extreme pressures and highly volatile thermal conditions. One tiny miscalculation can cause a massive explosion. LegendSpace plans to change this high-risk status quo entirely. They are upgrading their proprietary &#8220;Prime&#8221; intelligent simulation and design platform. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform uses deep-learning computational models to simulate complex fluid-flow dynamics in real time. Instead of constantsly blowing up metal chambers on a physical test stand, engineers can test thousands of virtual designs digitally. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This smart shift to computer-aided molecular modeling drastically compresses development timelines. Ultimately, it lowers the cost per launch and allows commercial satellite networks to scale rapidly.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nasdaq-sinks-asian-stocks-chinese-ai-advances/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Nasdaq Drops 2% As Investors Panic Over Chinese AI Advances</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Where the Funding Goes Next</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LegendSpace owes its momentum to its 35-year-old founder, </span><a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=lfgYtyoAAAAJ&amp;hl=en" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Chen Zhi</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Before launching the startup in early 2026, Chen served as a professor at the prestigious Peking University. He is also a Cambridge University alumnus who spent years specializing in complex combustion fluid dynamics. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chen realized that combining modern AI models with aerospace physics could solve decades-old design bottlenecks. His unique academic background and technical expertise gave investors the confidence to back the young company with substantial capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The capital injection will fund crucial static and thermal test fires for multiple liquid-propellant rocket engines. Second, the engineering team will continuously upgrade the &#8220;Prime&#8221; simulation software to enhance its predictive accuracy. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Finally, the remaining funds will go toward building scale manufacturing infrastructure. If the team executes this roadmap successfully, the cost of putting commercial payloads into orbit could plummet very soon.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ai-critic-ed-zitron-openai-might-collapse-stock-market/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Ed Zitron Says OpenAI Might Crash the Stock Market</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/legendspace-raises-29-5-million-ai-rocket-engines/" data-wpel-link="internal">LegendSpace Raises $29.5 Million in Angel Round To Develop AI-Driven Rocket Engines</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
