					<description><![CDATA[<p>Finding new physical materials, like ultrapure silicone, used in AI chipsets, can take decades of painstaking trial and error in dark labs. CuspAI is a Cambridge-based startup that wants to</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cuspai-raises-450-million-series-b-ai-materials-foundry/" data-wpel-link="internal">CuspAI Raises $450 Million in Series B Round To Launch AI Materials Foundry</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Finding new physical materials, like ultrapure silicone, used in AI chipsets, can take decades of painstaking trial and error in dark labs. CuspAI is a Cambridge-based startup that wants to make this process faster. In a massive milestone for the deep-tech sector, CuspAI raises $450 million in a </span><a href="https://medium.com/@CuspAI/launching-our-ai-materials-foundry-and-450-million-series-b-f5603d8259dd" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series B funding round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> to launch its ambitious AI Materials Foundry. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The startup uses advanced generative artificial intelligence to design molecules that the physical world desperately needs but does not yet possess. The team is determined to change how we manufacture everything from clean energy grids to advanced microchips.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">CupsAI’s Valuation Skyrockets To $2.6 Billion </span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This new injection of capital has sent the company’s market value skyrocketing. CuspAI now has a staggering $2.6 billion valuation, up from $520 in September 2025. Its Series B funding round was co-led by Kleiner Perkins and NEA. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CuspAI’s latest funding round also featured Jeff Bezos who threw his weight behind the round via Bezos Expeditions. Other notable backers include AMD Ventures, Lux Capital, and Britain’s Sovereign AI Venture Fund. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The rapid growth follows a successful Series A round of more than $100 million less than a year ago. This massive institutional interest highlights how eager the tech industry is to solve physical engineering bottlenecks. Investors clearly see this as the next trillion-dollar frontier.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nasdaq-sinks-asian-stocks-chinese-ai-advances/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Nasdaq Drops 2% As Investors Panick Over Chinese AI Advances</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Designing Materials That Can Actually Be Built</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many AI models are great at dreaming up theoretical concepts that fail completely in real-world environments. CuspAI is doing things differently. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2024 by Dr. Chad Edwards and Professor Max Welling, the startup blends generative AI with deep molecular simulations. Their proprietary software creates designs for materials that engineers can actually synthesize and build in standard facilities. The target use cases are massive. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They range from next-generation semiconductors and efficient vehicle batteries to carbon capture technologies. By focusing strictly on real-world manufacturing limits, the platform ensures its digital discoveries translate directly into physical hardware solutions.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/ai-critic-ed-zitron-openai-might-collapse-stock-market/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Ed Zitron Says OpenAI Might Crash the Stock Market</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The AI Materials Foundry Coalition</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203635" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203635" class="size-large wp-image-203635" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/CuspAI-team-1024x683.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-203635" class="wp-caption-text">CuspAI Team Photo</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Alongside the funding, the startup officially launched its highly anticipated AI Materials Foundry. This initiative serves as a massive global network that brings together clean data, compute power, laboratory access, and scientific expertise. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It is definitely not a solo effort. More than 45 founding corporate partners have already signed up to collaborate. </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvidia-5-trillion-milestone/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">NVIDIA</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, Meta, Samsung, Hyundai Motor Group, Lam Research, Tokyto Electron and Henkel are also joining the CuspAI effort. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This coalition aims to completely bridge the gap between abstract AI code and heavy industrial manufacturing. CuspAI is rapidly scaling its operational team to support this massive wave of international growth. The company is opening a new corporate office in Singapore to anchor its Asian expansion plans. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This strategic location adds to its existing hubs in Cambridge, Amsterdam, Berlin, and Tokyo. Former Google and Apple executive John Giannandrea will lead US operations. With top-tier talent and deep pockets, CuspAI will look to lead this industrial revolution.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/brinc-raises-125-million-for-911-response-drones/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>BRINC Raises $125M for 911 Response Drones in the U.S.</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cuspai-raises-450-million-series-b-ai-materials-foundry/" data-wpel-link="internal">CuspAI Raises $450 Million in Series B Round To Launch AI Materials Foundry</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
